Job Description: The Association of Statutory Health Insurance Dentists in Bavaria (KZVB) is looking for a full-time or part-time person to join the legal department as soon as possible  Fully qualified lawyers (m/f/d) Healthcare is a growth industry. Statutory health insurance alone spends over 200 billion euros a year on patient care. The KZVB ensures dental care in Bavaria, bills the health insurance companies for the services provided by Bavarian dentists and supports the practices in implementing legal requirements. It sees itself as a modern service company. As a corporation under public law, the KZVB also represents the interests of contract dentists vis-à-vis politicians and health insurance companies.
We offer you professional development opportunities in a varied and responsible area of ​​responsibility. The remuneration corresponds to the requirement profile: . There are also extensive social benefits including an attractive company pension scheme. You will work in a dedicated, collegial team characterized by great collegiality. You have a future-proof and modern workplace in the Munich district of Mittersendling with a direct S-Bahn connection and you can use the in-house canteen. With your work, you make an active contribution to ensuring that everyone in Bavaria has access to high-quality dental care close to where they live. Applicants (m/f/d) with a severe disability will be given preference if they are equally qualified.  Have we piqued your interest? Then welcome to our team!
Requirements for Applicant: 
Advanced knowledge: health care, legal representation

Job Description: Specialist consultant (m/f/d) - financial sales
Are you starting out in sales and always getting the best out of your customers? Would you like a job with good pay, appreciation of your work and great colleagues? Then we have something for you: For direct placement to a customer, we are looking for a specialist consultant (m/f/d) for financial sales as soon as possible. Where? You can easily do your job from the home office or directly in the office, which is located in the Pegnitz area.  Apply now
What you bring with you: * You live sales and communication, appear confident in dealing with customers * You have successfully completed your training as an insurance clerk (m/f/d) or bank clerk (m/f/d), for example. Alternatively, you have commercial training or professional experience in sales. * Knowledge of the financial and wealth sector desirable * However, career changers from other sales areas are also very welcome at our customer due to the extensive development opportunities
Requirements for Applicant: 
Basic knowledge: Order acceptance and processing
Advanced knowledge: Acquisition, customer advice and support, sales, field service

Job Description: Your tasks  You take care of the maintenance and administration of the IT audit list You regularly check and optimize implemented IT measures You are responsible for communication and coordination with the internal IT teams and across departments They ensure a smooth flow of information between the partners involved within the various IT teams  Your skills Completed commercial training or comparable qualification Confident handling of common Microsoft Office products (e.g. Excel) Independent way of working, as well as planning and organizational skills Initial experience in IT and a basic technical understanding are desirable High communication skills, teamwork and independent work We offer  With us you are not just wasting your time. Instead, we offer you a meaningful job and a career with real prospects! You will receive a fair salary and attractive additional benefits as a bonus. This also includes subsidies for childcare or company pension schemes. As an employee, you can enjoy attractive discounts. You will receive a 20% employee discount on your purchases in the Denns organic markets and you can use the monthly offers on our corporate benefits platform. We also offer you the option of leasing a company bike. Our annual working time account and the possibility of mobile working ensure a flexible organization of your working day. On our own eLearning platform "Wissen macht BIO" you can continue your education with a variety of courses or you can take advantage of our exciting range of further education options. We are looking for team players! That's why our annual team events don't miss out. Our company canteen at the Töpen site takes care of your physical well-being with discounted delicacies and a 100% organic kitchen.

Job Description: - New challenge in a constantly growing company | Work-life balance through flexible working hours and 30 days vacation  company profile Our mechanical engineering company based in Eschborn has been successfully active in the industry for many years and is looking to strengthen our finance team as soon as possible. As a accounts payable clerk (m/f/d) you are responsible for maintaining and monitoring accounts payable and contributing to the smooth running of our financial processes. area of ​​responsibility  -Maintenance and monitoring of accounts payable - Processing of incoming and outgoing payments - Creation of payment runs and dunning -Review and approval of invoices - Participate in the preparation of financial reports
requirement profile: -Successfully completed training as an accounts payable clerk (m/f/d) or comparable qualification - Experience in Accounts Payable would be an advantage - Good knowledge of MS Office and a common accounting program - Good knowledge of English is an advantage - Carefulness, reliability and ability to work in a team  Compensation Package  - A varied job in a modern mechanical engineering company -A performance-related salary and numerous social benefits - Regular training and further education opportunities -A nice and helpful team that looks forward to seeing you!

Job Description: - Established and internationally successful company with flat hierarchies|Responsibility for the entire consulting process. company profile The PageGroup is one of the world's leading consulting companies and is represented in 37 countries with around 7,000 employees. In Germany we are represented at locations in Düsseldorf, Frankfurt, Munich, Stuttgart, Hamburg, Cologne and Berlin. At the heart of our consulting business is the multitude of lives we positively transform. Our values ​​and our corporate culture are reflected in everything we do! Due to our ambitious growth path, we are currently looking for a People & Culture Business Consultant (m/f/d) to actively help shape our success story. Become part of a healthy, expanding company within a great team at our Munich location!  area of ​​responsibility  -You have a direct influence on the business success of your customers by advising them on strategy and organizational structure -You build your own network through loyal business relationships with customers from a wide variety of industries and sizes and communicate at eye level with top management -Your advice and support in the recruiting process as well as the creation of job advertisements contribute to the business success of your customers -You identify talent and conduct candidate interviews, as well as inspire and empower people to change their lives -You are responsible for customer pitches, conditions and contract negotiations -Your business development shapes your everyday work, with which you lead recruiting processes to success -You act as a sparring partner by bringing your customers and candidates together and making every recruiting process a success for all parties
requirement profile: -You want to make a difference and influence the success of each individual customer project - Solution orientation determines your entire way of working - Your positive attitude to life supports you in mastering difficult situations and in developing yourself further -You have a team spirit that helps us achieve our goals and celebrate our successes together -You have successfully completed your studies or comparable commercial training, ideally you have already been able to gain initial sales experience -You speak fluent German and English Compensation Package The employees are the focus at Page, for which the company has already been recognized several times as a top employer. A large-scale study by BRIGITTE counts the Page Group among the "best companies for women"!

We look forward to receiving your application! area of ​​responsibility  -Responsibility for a separate group of employees in payroll accounting in compliance with the legal framework (social security, wage tax, collective agreement and company agreements) -Maintenance of master data and collection of variable data with SAP HR -Processing the registration and certification system, creating reports and statistics - Participation in monthly, annual and quarterly financial statements as well as billing-related future projects -First point of contact for employees, social security agencies and authorities - Participation in travel expense management
requirement profile: - Commercial training or training in taxation or a comparable qualification -Several years of professional experience in the field of payroll or payroll accounting - Sound knowledge of social security, wage tax and labor law - Routine handling of EDP, especially with MS Office and preferably with the accounting software SAP HR - A high degree of independence and a structured and responsible way of working -Reliability and fun working in a team -Willingness to adapt working hours to the workload Compensation Package  - Crisis-proof workplace -Flexible working hours including the option of mobile working -Performance-linked wages -Extensive training -Advancement Opportunities -Employee discounts

Job Description: - Long-term professional perspective in an international environment | Friendly and collegial working atmosphere company profile Our large corporation based in Frankfurt am Main has been successfully active in the industry for many years and offers you the opportunity to develop in a dynamic and international working environment. As a financial accountant (m/f/d) you are an important part of our team and make a significant contribution to the financial success of our company.  area of ​​responsibility -Execution of financial accounting and accounting - Preparation of monthly, quarterly and annual financial statements -Maintenance and monitoring of accounts receivable and accounts payable - Processing of incoming and outgoing payments - Participation in the creation of budget plans and controls
requirement profile: -Successfully completed training as a financial accountant (m/f/d) or comparable qualification - Several years of professional experience in financial accounting - Good knowledge of MS Office and a common accounting program - Good knowledge of English is an advantage -Organizational and communication skills  Compensation Package -A demanding and varied job in an international environment -A performance-related remuneration and numerous social benefits such as company pension schemes and health promotion - Regular training and further education opportunities -A nice and helpful team that looks forward to seeing you!

Job Description: - Europes fastest growing board portal solution|This role will be a position in Germany to meet the demand for iBabs  company profile Europe's fastest growing board portal for 2,000+ organisations, iBabs empowers customers to quickly organize effective meetings and make good decisions confidently. Our software application is the best on the market to electronically distribute documents for Board and Committee meetings in a secure manner. We understand the work that goes into meetings - and how to streamline everything so it all flows smoothly on any device - confidentially, securely and automatically.  iBabs is present in Amsterdam, Brussels, London and Paris with every day over 200,000 users securely accessing their meeting documents and attending meetings - anytime, anywhere and on any device.  With our HQ in the Netherlands we have 20 years' experience of delivering meeting solutions. We have a wide variety of customers from PLCs, private companies, Banks, Insurers and Investment funds to charities, housing associations, NHS, State bodies, Councils and Government Ministries. With parent company Euronext we are currently expanding into Norway, Sweden, Finland, Denmark, Portugal, Spain, Germany and Italy. This role will be a position in Germany to meet the demand for iBabs in this market.  area of ​​responsibility As our trainer you are responsible for the successful onboarding and support of our board portal solution for our German-speaking clients within a broad range of organisations, from municipalities to ministries, from small healthcare organizations to large hospitals and from small businesses to large corporates. You will provide training sessions as part of the onboarding process for administrators/secretaries as well as to end-users. These training sessions may be in person or via video conference.  Administrators/secretaries receive a group three hour session so they are able to fully manage their iBabs site. End users who are usually board members and/or executive teams receive a one hour session. Within these sessions you may have those who are IT literate and only need five minutes support to get started right through to Independent board members who may be using technology for the first time. Every company is different as is every training session so you need to be adaptable with great communication skills (both face-to-face and online) However the reward is always the same, customers 'love' iBabs and become evangelical, often recommending us to other companies.  After the onboarding, you are the first point of contact for these clients. You will provide assistance and support for incoming queries and issues related to our board portal solution and any other related duties to support our German-speaking clients. To assist you we have second and third line support desks.  You may also be asked to train and support companies who are having a trial of iBabs. These require shortened training sessions but more hand-holding with weekly calls to ensure their trial is a success and they move to becoming a part of the iBabs family. In addition to the tasks described above, you will support the team in the English speaking market.
requirement profile: -Fluency in German and English is a must, professional capacity in another language is a plus -Excellent training skills and experience - Strong didactic and communication skills -Excellent technical knowledge and ability to interpret technical language for non-technical people - Strong customer support skills - Ability to troubleshoot and diagnose problems - Ability to communicate effectively -Writing and editing skills (to aid in writing and updating manuals) are a plus - Able to work in an autonomous and organized manner -The capacity to work well on your own or in a team Compensation Package  -To be part of a fast-growing and profitable company -To be part of an international and ambitious team - Competitive salary

requirement profile : -fluency german english , professional capacity language plus -excellent training skill experience - strong didactic communication skill -excellent technical knowledge ability interpret technical language non - technical people - strong customer support skill - ability troubleshoot diagnose problem - ability communicate effectively -write editing skill ( aid writing update manual ) plus - able work autonomous organized manner -the capacity work team compensation package -to fast - grow profitable company -to international ambitious team - competitive salary
wide variety customer plcs , private company , banks , insurers investment fund charity , housing association , nhs , state body , councils government ministries .
parent company euronext currently expand norway , sweden , finland , denmark , portugal , spain , germany italy .

Job Description: Our company We are a regional, owner-managed chain store company with a total of 5 branches in the greater Stuttgart area. We offer our customers a full range of paper and office stationery in modern, spacious shops. We work with all the leading manufacturers in the stationery industry. A special focus of our offer lies in the high-quality stationery and satchels. The SCHREIBfant branches are also heavily frequented lottery acceptance points.  Specialist salesman stationery (m/f/d) 25-40h/week - Stuttgart and Göppingen Your tasks * Advice and sale of stationery, tobacco products, press and lottery * Checkout and packaging of the goods sold * professional processing of incoming goods * Goods care and presentation in our shops We expect  * a well-groomed appearance and a positive charisma * Reliability, friendliness and pleasure in dealing with customers * Commitment, attentiveness and team spirit * Experience in sales, ideally of stationery or related products * Good knowledge of German in speaking and writing * prima is a certificate from lottery training – but not a requirement. We offer * a secure, long-term job in a family-run chain store * Pleasant and varied work in a committed team with flat hierarchies * Opportunities for advancement in a future-oriented company * performance-related payment * 6 weeks holiday * Attractive additional benefits, e.g. job ticket or childcare allowances * Employee discount * the good feeling of selling high-quality products Fits?

We offer you free further training as well as preventive and compulsory examinations. As a long-standing personnel service provider in the Hohenlohe district, we are strongly networked in the job market and therefore have well-known contacts to companies in which you can work. Regardless of whether you are looking for a job in the short, medium or long term, we offer you individual ""solutions with strategy"". Take your chance and become part of our team.  For security reasons, please send us your application documents in PDF format.  Our opening hours are from Monday to Friday 08.00 - 17.00. You can reach us by telephone on 07941 91890.  We look forward to you!  PS Personalservice GmbH Untere Torstrasse 13 74613 Öhringen 07941 9189-0 oehringen@psstrategie.de Machine and plant operator (m/f/d)

Job Description: Leipzig's energy future is important to us. That is why we are consciously breaking new ground in order to actively help shape the energy transition. With new ideas, expert knowledge and a lot of commitment, our around 1,200 employees ensure that Leipzig does not run out of energy - not today and not in the future. Give Leipzig energy too. Your tasks Meter assembly (assembly of measuring devices, identification of defects and manipulations as well as necessary documentation using handhelds (PDA / tablet / receiver / starter)) Construction, maintenance, repair and parameterization of radio systems for remote reading of device data Planning, announcement and implementation of post-assembly - and repair appointments as well as reading orders and post-reading appointments Ensuring the operability of the technical equipment in the objects and systems as well as instruction of service partners in assembly activities of submetering Support of the process manager or sales during inspections of properties for the preparation/evaluation of the measuring equipment Your profile Completed journeyman examination as a system mechanic (or similar) .Similar in the HLS area), mechatronics engineer, electrician with a focus on communications technology or a similar qualification with professional experience in the measurement service sector (m/f/d) Technical knowledge i In the context of the metering service business and metering, affinity and knowledge of communication technology in the metering service area (e.g. OMS, M-Bus or similar) Knowledge of MS Office products Willingness to work nationwide Good to know Unlimited full-time, 38 h/week Immediately in Leipzig Salary according to AVEU collective agreement Application stating the earliest possible starting date Please send your Application exclusively via our online form Our offer Company pension plan Annual special payment and 30 days of vacation Job ticket and bicycle leasing Insight into exciting energy projects of the future Work-life balance through modern working models and home office

Job Description: 
To strengthen our team, we are looking for an employee (m/f/d) in the field of medical technology as soon as possible. VAMED is a leading service provider in the healthcare sector. We plan, build and manage healthcare facilities throughout Germany. Our work is the basis for the safe operation of the technology in more than 440 hospitals. Our around 2,800 colleagues live a culture of openness and appreciation. We are always happy to welcome new colleagues who enrich our team with their different experiences and skills. With us, good ideas are always met with open ears. We offer great development opportunities and opportunities for advancement. As an employer with a future mission, we use individual and flexible workplace solutions. Full speed ahead towards the future! Discover your career at VAMED, we look forward to seeing you. Your benefits: Friendly and team-oriented working atmosphere and employee events Permanent contact person during induction and experienced colleagues Individual training and further education opportunities through our VAMED Academy Participation and creative freedom Secure workplace in the healthcare sector Flexible working hours Mobile working Subsidy to company pension scheme Jobrad und Team Corporate benefits discounts for the VAMED Vitality World and for fitness studios Your tasks: Carrying out inspections, maintenance and repairs on medical devices and systems Carrying out safety-related and metrological checks in accordance with the MPBetreibV and the StrISchG Documentation of all measures in the maintenance program Supporting the users of medical devices in all technical Questions Completion of tasks in the medical technology workshop What you bring with you: Execution of inspections, maintenance and repairs tures on medical devices and systems Carrying out safety and metrological controls in accordance with the MPBetreibV and the StrISchG Documentation of all measures in the maintenance program Supporting the users of medical devices with all technical questions Completion of tasks that arise in the medical technology workshop Is that your job? We look forward to meeting you! Please send us your application documents, stating your salary expectations and your earliest possible starting date. Your contact person: Ms. Kahlert-Wongpeng Medical Technology Division Tel: 030 246 269 310

Basic knowledge: welding
Advanced knowledge: metal construction, assembly (metal, plant construction)

Job Description: Industrial mechanic (m/f/d) assembly job code  The KMS Group is a service company in the field of human resources.  Our portfolio includes employee leasing, personnel placement, outsourcing and on-site management in the fields of aviation, vehicle construction, mechanical engineering, steel construction, warehousing / logistics, finance / office and engineering. We offer you an innovative and challenging job, an attractive salary and good development opportunities.  Our customer has its headquarters in Wangen im Allgäu, which operates in Europe and worldwide with a total of around 1,600 employees. Through the development and production of filling systems and process systems, our client manufactures the customer-specific requirements. Become part of a healthy, 100-year-old family business in mechanical and plant engineering! Your tasks  - You assemble mechanical components including functional testing - You put together parts using bills of materials and pay attention to completeness - Confidently and independently you assemble assemblies according to drawings and later machines and systems - Through the targeted use of measuring and testing equipment, you ensure the perfect quality of our products - Analyze errors and glitches  your qualifications - Successfully completed training as an industrial mechanic (m/f/d), mechatronics technician (m/f/d) or a comparable qualification. - First professional experience in pre-assembly and final assembly in mechanical engineering. - You are a team player and passionate about mechanics. - You are flexible and work project-related if necessary in a 2-shift system. We offer  - We help with your personal development! - No boredom! - Challenging tasks, interesting environment - Expiry Date? - Permanent employment

task - assemble mechanical component include functional testing - part bill material pay attention completeness - confidently independently assemble assembly accord drawing later machine system - target use measure testing equipment , ensure perfect quality product - analyze error glitche qualification - successfully complete training industrial mechanic ( m / f / d ) , mechatronic technician ( m / f / d ) comparable qualification .
portfolio include employee leasing , personnel placement , outsourcing - site management field aviation , vehicle construction , mechanical engineering , steel construction , warehousing / logistic , finance / office engineering .
- professional experience pre - assembly final assembly mechanical engineering . - team player passionate mechanic .

Job Description: Electrician (m/f/d) installation and control cabinet construction  Job code BEBA-853-8534 The KMS Group is a service company in the field of human resources.  Our portfolio includes employee leasing, personnel placement, outsourcing and on-site management in the fields of aviation, vehicle construction, mechanical engineering, steel construction, warehousing / logistics, finance / office and engineering. We offer you an innovative and challenging job, an attractive salary and good development opportunities.  Our customer has its headquarters in Wangen im Allgäu, which operates in Europe and worldwide with a total of around 1,600 employees. Through the development and production of filling systems and process systems, our client manufactures the customer-specific requirements. Become part of a healthy, 100-year-old family business in mechanical and plant engineering! Your tasks  - In a team of 20 colleagues you are responsible for the construction, installation, wiring and commissioning of control cabinets - You will install and lay cables on complex machines - You carry out VDE tests - You travel to the customer for commissioning - Analyzing malfunctions and errors your qualifications  - Successfully completed training as an electrician (m/f/d), electronics technician (m/f/d) or a comparable qualification - Ideally, first experience in control cabinet construction and machine installation - You are a team player and enthusiastic about electrical engineering. - You are flexible and like to travel We offer - We help with your personal development! - No boredom! - Challenging tasks, interesting environment - Expiry Date? - Permanent employment

task - team 20 colleague responsible construction , installation , wiring commission control cabinet - install lay cable complex machine - carry vde test - travel customer commission - analyze malfunction error qualification - successfully complete training electrician ( m / f / d ) , electronics technician ( m / f / d ) comparable qualification - ideally , experience control cabinet construction machine installation - team player enthusiastic electrical engineering .
portfolio include employee leasing , personnel placement , outsourcing - site management field aviation , vehicle construction , mechanical engineering , steel construction , warehousing / logistic , finance / office engineering .
job description : electrician ( m / f / d ) installation control cabinet construction job code beba-853 - 8534 kms group service company field human resource .

Job Description: Plant mechanic (m/f/d) Tank and container builder  Job code BEBA-853-8535 The KMS Group is a service company in the field of human resources.  Our portfolio includes employee leasing, personnel placement, outsourcing and on-site management in the fields of aviation, vehicle construction, mechanical engineering, steel construction, warehousing / logistics, finance / office and engineering.  We offer you an innovative and challenging job, an attractive salary and good development opportunities. Our customer has its headquarters in Wangen im Allgäu, which operates in Europe and worldwide with a total of around 1,600 employees. Through the development and production of filling systems and process systems, our client manufactures the customer-specific requirements. The team looks forward to your application!  Your tasks - You manufacture assemblies according to design drawings - You set up systems and attach welding bevels - Tacking, welding, straightening and testing of demanding assemblies - You check parts for distortion and assemble them into complete constructions - They document test results and apply test marks your qualifications  - Successfully completed training as a plant mechanic (m/f/d) specializing in welding technology or a comparable qualification - First professional experience in special machine construction - Skilled craftsmanship

task - manufacture assembly accord design drawing - set system attach welding bevel - tack , welding , straighten testing demand assembly - check part distortion assemble complete construction - document test result apply test mark qualification - successfully complete training plant mechanic ( m / f / d ) specialize welding technology comparable qualification - professional experience special machine construction - skilled craftsmanship
portfolio include employee leasing , personnel placement , outsourcing - site management field aviation , vehicle construction , mechanical engineering , steel construction , warehousing / logistic , finance / office engineering .

Job Description: Plant mechanic (m/f/d) laboratory assembly  Job code BEBA-853-8536  The KMS Group is a service company in the field of human resources. Our portfolio includes employee leasing, personnel placement, outsourcing and on-site management in the fields of aviation, vehicle construction, mechanical engineering, steel construction, warehousing / logistics, finance / office and engineering.  We offer you an innovative and challenging job, an attractive salary and good development opportunities. Our customer has its headquarters in Wangen im Allgäu, which operates in Europe and worldwide with a total of around 1,600 employees. Through the development and production of filling systems and process systems, our client manufactures the customer-specific requirements. The team looks forward to your application!  Your tasks - Through careful assembly and installation of our laboratory products at the customer, you will ensure optimal results - They complete and connect the piping system and connect the media piping to the on-site transfer points - You check the piping systems for function and tightness, create the associated protocol and carry out the quality inspection - With your communicative nature, you skillfully conduct coordination and coordination talks with other companies and hand over the sanitary facility, including user instructions, to the customer your qualifications - You have completed training as a plant mechanic (m/f/d) SHK or a comparable qualification - You have manual skills and technical understanding and also want to familiarize yourself with topics such as electronics and everything to do with laboratory furniture - Smooth communication within the team and with customers is good manners for you - You convince with an independent and result-oriented way of working - You have a driver's license and look forward to exciting assembly work (Monday to Friday). We offer  - We help with your personal development! - No boredom! - Challenging tasks, interesting environment - Expiry Date? - Permanent employment

task - careful assembly installation laboratory product customer , ensure optimal result - complete connect piping system connect medium piping - site transfer point - check piping system function tightness , create associate protocol carry quality inspection - communicative nature , skillfully conduct coordination coordination talk company hand sanitary facility , include user instruction , customer qualification - complete training plant mechanic ( m / f / d ) shk comparable qualification - manual skill technical understanding want familiarize topic electronic laboratory furniture - smooth communication team customer good manner - convince independent result - orient way working - driver license look forward exciting assembly work ( monday friday ) .
portfolio include employee leasing , personnel placement , outsourcing - site management field aviation , vehicle construction , mechanical engineering , steel construction , warehousing / logistic , finance / office engineering .

Job Description: Wood mechanic (m/f/d) Job code BEBA-853-8537  The KMS Group is a service company in the field of human resources. Our portfolio includes employee leasing, personnel placement, outsourcing and on-site management in the fields of aviation, vehicle construction, mechanical engineering, steel construction, warehousing / logistics, finance / office and engineering.  We offer you an innovative and challenging job, an attractive salary and good development opportunities.  Our customer has its headquarters in Wangen im Allgäu, which operates in Europe and worldwide with a total of around 1,600 employees. Through the development and production of filling systems and process systems, our client manufactures the customer-specific requirements. The team looks forward to your application!  Your tasks  - You operate the woodworking machines with confidence and thus ensure optimal conditions for the downstream production steps - You carry out regular checks of dimensions, drilling and milling patterns. - In the event of deviations, keep a cool head and carry out the necessary parameter adjustments or tool changes at an early stage - The CNC controlled woodworking machine, reprogram if necessary  your qualifications - You have completed training as a carpenter (m/f/d), carpenter (m/f/d), wood mechanic (m/f/d) or a comparable qualification - You enjoy the wood product and would like to work in 2 shifts - You are characterized by manual dexterity and spatial imagination - Ideally, you already have professional experience in the operation and maintenance of woodworking machines We offer  - We help with your personal development! - No boredom! - Challenging tasks, interesting environment - Expiry Date? - Permanent employment

- event deviation , cool head carry necessary parameter adjustment tool change early stage - cnc control woodworking machine , reprogram necessary qualification - complete training carpenter ( m / f / d ) , carpenter ( m / f / d ) , wood mechanic ( m / f / d ) comparable qualification - enjoy wood product like work 2 shift - characterize manual dexterity spatial imagination - ideally , professional experience operation maintenance woodworke machine offer - help personal development !
portfolio include employee leasing , personnel placement , outsourcing - site management field aviation , vehicle construction , mechanical engineering , steel construction , warehousing / logistic , finance / office engineering .

Job Description: Specialist (m/f/d) mechanical documentation Job code BEBA-864-8650  The KMS Group is a service company in the field of human resources.  Our portfolio includes employee leasing, personnel placement, outsourcing and on-site management in the fields of aviation, vehicle construction, mechanical engineering, steel construction, warehousing / logistics, finance / office and engineering. We offer you an innovative and challenging job, an attractive salary and good development opportunities.  Our international customer is the pioneer in the construction of highly innovative production and automation systems in the region and worldwide! For the team at the Mindelheim location, we are looking for an inquisitive and attentive colleague (m/f/d) with immediate effect. Your tasks  - You take over the creation of mechanical drawing documentation of our plants according to the diverse requirements of our various customers - You prepare both the data formats of the 2D and 3D drawings as well as the master and parts list data from our SAP system according to customer specifications - You are responsible for the creation of customer-specific parts lists and various project lists according to the specifications - You participate in the constant improvement process to automate the recurring processes your qualifications  - Completed vocational training as a technical product designer, in a technical profession, each with a fable for IT solutions - Good MS Office skills - English knowledge in spoken and written - You are characterized by an independent, structured and conscientious way of working - You have the ability to work in a team and willingness to learn - Basic knowledge of AutoCAD and Siemens NX or comparable CAD systems - Basic knowledge of SAP desirable We offer - We help with your personal development! - No boredom! - Challenging tasks, interesting environment - Expiry Date? - Permanent employment

task - creation mechanical drawing documentation plant accord diverse requirement customer - prepare datum format 2d 3d drawing master part list datum sap system accord customer specification - responsible creation customer - specific part list project list accord specification - participate constant improvement process automate recur process qualification - complete vocational training technical product designer , technical profession , fable solution - good ms office skill - english knowledge speak write - characterize independent , structured conscientious way working - ability work team willingness learn - basic knowledge autocad siemens nx comparable cad system - basic knowledge sap desirable offer - help personal development !
portfolio include employee leasing , personnel placement , outsourcing - site management field aviation , vehicle construction , mechanical engineering , steel construction , warehousing / logistic , finance / office engineering .

As a family trading company for building materials of all kinds, we are looking for support for our team of employees so that our customers can continue to receive top service and good advice.
Our requirements: - Completed commercial training Career starters welcome! - Motivation and willingness to perform - A friendly and confident demeanor   We offer you a secure job in a successful company with a good working atmosphere! Interested? Then we look forward to receiving your detailed application!

Job Description: The state of Berlin is the largest employer in the region. Around 130,000 employees in the immediate state administration work every day to ensure that Berlin functions as a vibrant metropolis and as a home for around 3.65 million people. The staff of the general non-technical administrative service form the backbone of the Berlin administration.  The Senate Department for Education, Youth and Family is responsible for ensuring that all Berliners have good educational opportunities - from early childhood education in daycare to a good school-leaving certificate for vocational training or university studies. It creates the framework for young people and families to feel at home in this city and guarantees support and encouragement in all walks of life. In addition to the approximately 42,000 employees at the Berlin schools, more than 2,000 employees work in the specialist departments of the ministerial part of the Senate Administration for fundamental and operational tasks.   To strengthen its team, Department V - Family and Early Childhood Education - of the Senate Department for Education, Youth and Family is looking for staff (several positions) for the area of ​​responsibility from February 1st, 2023 Clerk in the area of ​​data warehouse - integrated software Berlin youth welfare (DWH-ISBJ) including statistics in the working group statistics and data management (m/f/d)  Code number 29/23  unlimited,
• For the complete job requirements, please refer to the requirement profile: under the button ""further information"" (at the bottom of the advertisement). We offer you • an interesting, varied and challenging job in which you can help shape important areas of life in the city of Berlin. • the opportunity to further develop your personal skills by taking advantage of our wide range of technical and non-technical further education and training opportunities and thus opening up career opportunities for yourself.   • An attractive payment, which is based on the TV-L for employees who are not covered by a collective agreement or on the AT payment guidelines of the State of Berlin for employees who are not covered by a collective agreement, and on the Berlin State Salary Act for civil servants. • an additional old-age provision via the VBL (Federal and State Pension Fund).   • the compatibility of career and family through flexible working hours and the possibility of part-time employment within the framework of official needs. If necessary, you can use a parent-child room or, depending on the available places, a place in a nearby day-care center can be arranged. We are certified by the berufundfamilie audit as a family-friendly employer. • A company health management whose offers (e.g. diverse sporting activities) are intended to maintain your health. • good accessibility of your workplace by public transport, for which we can provide you with a BVG job ticket.   • a collegial working atmosphere in a diverse, tolerant and cosmopolitan administration, in which we are committed to equal opportunities. Severely handicapped people and people of equal status will be given preferential treatment if they have the same qualifications. Please indicate in your application if you have a severe disability. Applications from people with a migration background who meet the hiring requirements are expressly encouraged.
Can you find yourself in the profile? Then we look forward to receiving your application by March 20th, 2023 using the “apply now” button below. For the complete job requirements, please refer to the requirement profile: under the button ""further information"" (at the bottom of the advertisement).  Please enclose a CV in tabular form with your application ...

Around 130,000 employees in the immediate state administration work every day to ensure that Berlin functions as a vibrant metropolis and as a home for around 3.65 million people. The staff of the general non-technical administrative service form the backbone of the Berlin administration. The Senate Department for Education, Youth and Family  is responsible for ensuring that all Berliners have good educational opportunities - from early childhood education in daycare to a good school-leaving certificate for vocational training or university studies. It creates the framework for young people and families to feel at home in this city and guarantees support and encouragement in all walks of life. In addition to the approximately 42,000 employees at the Berlin schools, more than 2,000 employees work in the specialist departments of the ministerial part of the Senate Administration for fundamental and operational tasks. To strengthen its team, the Senate Department for Education, Youth and Family - Department I - is looking for an employee for the area of ​​responsibility in the advisory and support center for inclusive education in the Friedrichshain-Kreuzberg region from August 1st, 2023 until July 31st, 2024  Secretarial and administrative tasks in a counseling and support center for inclusive education of a regional branch of Dept. I (m/f/d) Code number 30/23  Temporary, deputizing for an employee (release due to a sabbatical)
Can you find yourself in the profile? Then we look forward to receiving your application by March 6th, 2023 using the “apply now” button below. For the complete job requirements, please refer to the requirement profile: under the button ""further information"" (at the bottom of the advertisement). Please enclose a curriculum vitae in tabular form, a current certificate or a current official appraisal as well as complete documents for your training and study qualifications with your application. It is not necessary to send or upload a (passport) photo.  ...
Requirements for Applicant: 
Basic knowledge: Cost and performance accounting, office and administrative work

strengthen team , senate department education , youth family - department - look employee area ​​responsibility advisory support center inclusive education friedrichshain - kreuzberg region august 1st , 2023 july 31st , 2024 secretarial administrative task counseling support center inclusive education regional branch dept .

Job Description: The state of Berlin is the largest employer in the region. Around 130,000 employees in the immediate state administration work every day to ensure that Berlin functions as a vibrant metropolis and as a home for around 3.65 million people. The staff of the general non-technical administrative service form the backbone of the Berlin administration.  The Senate Department for Education, Youth and Family is responsible for ensuring that all Berliners have good educational opportunities - from early childhood education in daycare to a good school-leaving certificate for vocational training or university studies. It creates the framework for young people and families to feel at home in this city and guarantees support and encouragement in all walks of life. In addition to the approximately 42,000 employees at the Berlin schools, more than 2,000 employees work in the specialist departments of the ministerial part of the Senate Administration for fundamental and operational tasks.   Department V - Family and Early Childhood Education - of the Senate Department for Education, Youth and Family is now looking for an employee to strengthen its team Housekeeping clerk as part of the Federal Foundation "Early Help" (m/f/d)  Code number 26/23  unlimited,
• Persons who will probably only acquire the formal requirements specified in the requirement profile: in the next 6 months after the application deadline can also apply for the job advertisement (please enclose relevant evidence such as interim certificates).
• For the complete job requirements, please refer to the requirement profile: under the button ""further information"" (at the bottom of the advertisement). We offer you  • an interesting, varied and challenging job in which you can help shape important areas of life in the city of Berlin.  • the opportunity to further develop your personal skills by taking advantage of our wide range of technical and non-technical further education and training opportunities and thus opening up career opportunities for yourself. • An attractive payment, which is based on the TV-L for employees who are not covered by a collective agreement or on the AT payment guidelines of the State of Berlin for employees who are not covered by a collective agreement, and on the Berlin State Salary Act for civil servants. • an additional old-age provision via the VBL (Federal and State Pension Fund).   • the compatibility of career and family through flexible working hours and the possibility of part-time employment within the framework of official needs. If necessary, you can use a parent-child room or, depending on the available places, a place in a nearby day-care center can be arranged. We are certified by the berufundfamilie audit as a family-friendly employer. • A company health management whose offers (e.g. diverse sporting activities) are intended to maintain your health.   • good accessibility of your workplace by public transport, for which we can provide you with a BVG job ticket. • a collegial working atmosphere in a diverse, tolerant and cosmopolitan administration, in which we are committed to equal opportunities. Severely handicapped people and people of equal status will be given preferential treatment if they have the same qualifications. Please indicate in your application if you have a severe disability. Applications from people with a migration background who meet the hiring requirements are expressly encouraged.
Can you find yourself in the profile? Then we look forward to receiving your application by March 20th, 2023 using the “apply now” button below. For the full job requirements, please refer to the requirement profile: under the button  ...

Job Description: Become a postman for letters in Hattingen what we offer * €14.34 standard hourly wage – plus holiday and Christmas bonuses * You can start immediately full-time for a limited period of time, 38.50 hours/week * A crisis-proof workplace, guaranteed salary increase according to the collective agreement and punctual salary payments * Possibility of overtime payment * Free provision of quality workwear * Detailed instruction (paid) - we will get you ready for the delivery * Permanent takeover and development opportunities (e.g. site manager) possible with good performance and open positions * Attractive employee offers such as employer-financed company pension schemes, bicycle leasing, discounts from mobile phone providers, etc. Your duties as a postman for letters * Delivery of letters in 5 working days * Accept and sort mail items * Delivery by bike or on foot What you offer as a deliverer * You can converse in German * You ride your bike safely in traffic * You are weatherproof and can tackle things well * You are reliable and stick to it  Become a postman at Deutsche Post DHL  As a mail carrier, you make the people in your district happy every day and deliver the mail to them. You walk or cycle five working days a week (between Monday and Saturday) and don't let the weather spoil your mood. We also welcome career changers or students, because you count as you are! We look forward to receiving your application as a deliverer, preferably online! Simply click on the 'Apply' button – even without a CV.  CONNECTING PEOPLE, IMPROVING LIVES #becomeoneofus #become one of us mailman #postmanforletters

Job Description: ISZ GmbH operates the CAFM control center of the FHH. This supports the authorities, districts, state companies and city-owned companies in the introduction and regular operation of CAFM and in this context also looks after their own CAFM systems. -  Configuration and maintenance of the IT systems of the CAFM control center and integration into the general IT architecture  - Configuration and parameterization of the CAFM system speedikon C in cooperation with the manufacturer  - Development and creation of customer-specific reports and configurations in the CAFM system  -  Developments, further developments and acceptance of the software with the software manufacturer as well as implementation of tests and documentation/quality assurance -  General support as well as assistance with fault analysis and technical troubleshooting -  Support of the CAFM control center with tasks in the wider IT environment  - Support in the operation of the associated infrastructures in the area of ​​responsibility  - Communication with or control of IT service providers in the area of ​​responsibility  -  Support in ensuring and further developing general IT operations, IT processes and IT security together with external IT service providers -  Advice and support in the development, implementation and further development of interfaces to third-party systems and mobile / web-based applications -  Management and participation of/in internal IT projects  - Responsibilities for data protection and data security of the company  - Experience in the administration, installation and configuration of client and server hardware and software as well as network components  -  Experience in the planning, administration and further development of IT infrastructure, networks and security issues -  Knowledge of the Microsoft environment (Windows Server 2012 - 2019, MS SQL) -

- configuration maintenance system cafm control center integration general architecture - configuration parameterization cafm system speedikon c cooperation manufacturer - development creation customer - specific report configuration cafm system - development , development acceptance software software manufacturer implementation test documentation / quality assurance - general support assistance fault analysis technical troubleshooting - support cafm control center task wide environment - support operation associate infrastructure area ​​responsibility - communication control service provider area ​​responsibility - support ensure develop general operation , process security external service provider - advice support development , implementation development interface - party system mobile / web - base application - management participation / internal project - responsibilities datum protection datum security company - experience administration , installation configuration client server hardware software network component - experience planning , administration development infrastructure , network security issue - knowledge microsoft environment ( windows server 2012 - 2019 , ms sql ) -
support authority , district , state company city - own company introduction regular operation cafm context look cafm system .
job description : isz gmbh operate cafm control center fhh .

Job Description: As a communication point between tenants and landlords, the ISZ service area MVM-Consulting (MVM = tenant-landlord-model) advises the tenants in a team and in an interdisciplinary manner throughout the entire (structural) development process from service phase 1 as part of the registration and analysis of requirements, e.g. Profitability analyses, interface definitions, plausibility checks of life cycle costs or specific acceptances until the property is moved in and used.  Our ISZ service area is the communication point between tenants and landlords. We are experts in MVM (tenant-landlord-model) consulting. As a project manager, you will advise the tenants on the entire (structural) development process, both in a team and on an interdisciplinary basis. You accompany our tenants from service phase 1, as part of the registration and analysis of requirements, in rental contract negotiations, profitability analyses, interface definitions, the plausibility check of life cycle costs or with specific acceptances up to moving in and using the property. - You will be involved in the neutral advice of the tenant project as well as in the determination of needs and quality assurance of external needs analyses. - In addition, you accompany the users and users in tenant-landlord projects through almost all service phases and in the structure and design of tenant projects. - You take over the initial check and documentation of requirement notifications as well as the inclusion in the requirement register and the regular reporting on requirement notifications. - You are an accompanist in checking the coverage of needs for inventory, rental and purchase. - With your eye for detail, you check the plausibility of rental cost calculations by landlords. - The (formal) consultation and examination of the LOI, as well as the examination of the rent, compliance with standards or deviations, the past project steps, WU and NWA are also part of your area of ​​responsibility. - You take over the accompaniment when handing over the rental property i.Z.m. ABH (defects, unfulfilled requirements, etc.) and the plausibility check of the contractually agreed cost items.  Must have - You have a university degree (bachelor's degree or equivalent) in the field of civil engineering, architecture, real estate management, a comparable field or skills and experience equivalent to these university degrees. - In addition, you have already gained several years of professional experience related to the advertised position. - You have a strong customer orientation as well as very good communication skills and negotiation skills in dealing with stakeholders. - You are assertive and have an independent, analytical and creative approach. - You love to constantly improve internal and external processes. - If you also have a strong team spirit and enjoy working with interdisciplinary teams, then we should get to know each other.  Nice to have  - Many years of practical experience in the planning, control and implementation of building construction measures would be desirable. - Ideally, you have acquired additional qualifications and certificates in project management (IPMA or similar). - You have good knowledge of construction contract law and public procurement as well as municipal real estate management (tenant-landlord model). - Basic business knowledge is also an advantage.  - Work-life balance With us you get flextime, 30 days...

job description : communication point tenant landlord , isz service area mvm - consulting ( mvm = tenant - landlord - model ) advise tenant team interdisciplinary manner entire ( structural ) development process service phase 1 registration analysis requirement , e.g. profitability analysis , interface definition , plausibility check life cycle cost specific acceptance property move .
accompany tenant service phase 1 , registration analysis requirement , rental contract negotiation , profitability analysis , interface definition , plausibility check life cycle cost specific acceptance move property .

Job Description: In this function, you will assume responsibility for the implementation of competent, customer-friendly and result-oriented rental and contract management in coordination with the team and department management.  New rental of objects  - On the basis of needs analyses, you determine the need for new rental properties. - You are in charge of finding, examining and selecting locations and buildings considering any urban options. - You carry out contract negotiations on object designs and conditions and conclude rental agreements. - You create benefit analyzes and decision templates.  inventory management - You are responsible for compliance with and changes to existing contracts. - You identify area and cost optimizations in the managed portfolio. - You advise our customers and keep an eye on our scheduled resubmissions. - You are responsible for tracking defects in our existing properties. - You are also responsible for terminating leases and negotiating and terminating contracts.  - You have completed a (technical) university degree in the field of real estate management or have completed training as a real estate clerk and further training as a real estate specialist or a comparable qualification. - You have already gained sound professional experience in a comparable area. - You have very good knowledge of the market. - The secure application of the legal basis in commercial tenancy law is a matter of course for you. - You have experience working with SAP or other rental management systems. - Your appearance is confident in every situation, you have convincing communication skills and negotiation security. - You have an independent, solution-oriented and structured approach. - If you are also a team player, reliable and very committed, then we should get to know each other. -  work-life balance With us you get flextime, 30 days vacation and more days off on Christmas Eve and New Year's Eve. You also have the opportunity for sabbaticals and temporary part-time work. -  Attractive employer benefits We also compensate any overtime work within the framework of the collective agreement of the AVH. In addition, you will receive a special annual payment and a 50% subsidy for the HVV Proficard.  -  Work-life balance You shape your everyday work – through mobile working and flexible working hours without core working hours.  - Corporate Health Management  With our company doctor and a health cost subsidy, we support you in promoting your health.  - Diversity and Equal Opportunities  We live diversity, tolerance and equal opportunities and offer you a working atmosphere with freedom for personal and professional development, short decision-making processes and flat hierarchies in a team characterized by mutual respect. -  More Benefits  Modern working environments in the heart of the city of Hamburg, bicycle leasing, bicycle parking spaces on site, company events, company pension scheme. Apply anyway and convince us with your personality! We don't expect you to already be able to do everything. Just bring courage and passion with you to...

- independent , solution - orient structured approach . - team player , reliable committed , know .
- diversity equal opportunities live diversity , tolerance equal opportunity offer work atmosphere freedom personal professional development , short decision - make process flat hierarchy team characterize mutual respect .
job description : function , assume responsibility implementation competent , customer - friendly result - orient rental contract management coordination team department management .

Job Description: About Us  Junge Die Bäckerei has dedicated itself to “genuine enjoyment”. prescribed since 1897. The family business has been owner-managed for four generations and is much more than a bakery. The pillars of success include the 4,300 passionate employees as well as innovative spirit and high quality standards for baked goods, snacks and coffee specialties. Junge has received multiple awards for its products, employees and innovations, and is now one of the leading companies in the bakery and quick-service restaurant sectors. The company, with around 200 stores, has developed into a coveted brand throughout Northern Germany and Berlin.  Our sales staff appreciate the family atmosphere, the structured work and the security of a large, medium-sized company.  Trainee (m/f/d) Area Sales Manager - Berlin Would you like to contribute your skills to the commercial and personal support of our business? Would you like to take on responsibility, but you are still missing a few ingredients? As a trainee (m/f/d) for area sales management in the Berlin region, we offer you an intensive, structured training period for your subsequent job as area sales management. Join an expanding family business that offers you attractive benefits.

Job Description: View job here  The senior citizens' facilities of the district of Würzburg gGmbH were founded in 1998. It employs over 500 people at eight locations. In addition to long-term and short-term care as well as day care, the holistic care of dementia sufferers and those in need of serious care is an important concern of the senior citizens' facilities. Nursing staff (m/f/d) for the living area "" Nursing""  * Full or part time * 97285 Roettingen, Germany * Without work experience * 02/20/23 In the senior center in Röttingen, a living area is being built according to the “care” concept. This concept is designed for the care, support and support of people between the ages of 18 and 65 who, due to a disability and/or neurological disease, are in need of care within the meaning of long-term care insurance and are therefore classified in a care level. The aim is to maintain the physical, mental and emotional independence of the residents for as long as possible.  We are therefore looking for nurses, nursing assistants and nursing assistants (m/f/d) for the senior center in Röttingen as soon as possible.  Your tasks * Support for or provision of basic care or basic and treatment care as well as care and support for the residents, depending on their qualifications * Recognizing and assessing the physical, mental, emotional and social needs as well as strengthening and promoting the skills of the residents * Planning, implementation and digital documentation of all care processes * Acquisition of care-related household activities * Interdisciplinary and constructive cooperation with all professional groups and relatives    your profile * Completed three-year vocational training as a geriatric nurse / nursing specialist or nursing specialist / health worker and nurse (m/f/d) or * Completed one-year vocational training as a nursing assistant (m/f/d) or comparable qualifications or * Nursing assistants with and without prior knowledge. We also welcome career changers. We offer * Crisis-proof employer * permanent employment * industry-standard remuneration according to collective agreement, depending on qualifications * 30 vacation days plus additional vacation for the care of children or relatives in need of care * Up to €100 childcare subsidy per month * Employee events (company bowling, eating asparagus, theme party, Christmas party) * Participation in the corporate benefits program * Car and e-bike leasing * Company subscription for local public transport * Company health management with subsidies for VHS courses for health promotion, working time credit for check-ups, and much more. Curious? Then we look forward to receiving your application!  If you have any questions about the “care” concept, please contact the care service manager, Mr Artur Hild, on 09338 9807-0.  If you have any questions about the application process, please do not hesitate to contact our nursing staff officer, Ms. Vanessa Drösler, on 0931 8009-1103. Senior citizens' facilities in the district of Würzburg Zeppelinstrasse 67 97074 Würzburg www.senioreneinrichtungen.info  Imprint | Data protection  Powered by softgarden

Because you see complexity as an opportunity and both quality and sustainability are important criteria in your work, we would like to work with you on the solutions of tomorrow. With trust, transparency and appreciation, we create sustainable healthcare together - locally, in regions, countries and worldwide. This is sharing expertise.  (Senior) Manager (m/f/d) Pharmaceutical Development Code number DEML429042-75849  For our Center of Excellence Vascular Systems of the B. Braun division Aesculap located in Berlin, we are looking for a (Senior) Manager (m/f/d) Pharmaceutical Development. tasks and responsibilities  * Management, coordination and implementation of development projects in the field of interventional cardiology and related fields * Development, application and adaptation of coating technologies for drug-coated medical devices for intravascular use * Development, prototyping and testing of drug-coated medical devices * Planning and creation of design specifications and product specifications * Coordination and evaluation of test series for design verification and product registration according to valid standards * Know-how transfer in development / production, particularly regarding coating processes, as part of the establishment of development products in routine production * Creation of MDR-compliant approval documentation (preparatory work for STED and eCTD) for product registration within and outside the CE area Technical skills  * Successfully completed studies in engineering or natural sciences (medical technology, mechanical engineering, pharmacy, chemistry, etc.) or comparable qualification * Several years of professional experience in the product development of medical devices, especially in the area of ​​combination products * Experience in the field of plant construction and process validation, especially in medical technology as well as knowledge of the relevant standards * Very good knowledge of spoken and written English * Confident use of MS Office applications * Intercultural competence and willingness to travel Personal skills * You appear ready to perform and take responsibility * You set high quality standards and act cost-consciously * Constructive interaction is a matter of course for you * You communicate clearly and responsibly our range  Take part in a corporate culture that actively promotes constructive exchange with colleagues, customers and partners. Work with us to improve people's lives in a sustainable way. We offer you a wide range of tasks and excellent development opportunities as well as attractive remuneration with extensive social benefits in a dynamic family business. benefits  * Flexible working hours * Attractive location in the federal capital Berlin * BVG job ticket * You can find more benefits on our website your next step  Enrich your career and apply via the global job market on our website (www.bbraun.de).

Job Description: You can now hire to strengthen our team as a  SPECIALIST (M/F/D) FOR GLOBAL SEA FREIGHT TRANSPORT As a specialist (m/f/d) for global sea freight transport, you are well networked and are available to advise and support our customers - from Ehingen or Bremerhaven, hybrid or remote. They negotiate with shipowners, prepare offers, organize freight space and connecting transports. Scheduling, order entry and on-carriage are done with ease. You will be part of a great team with a lot of know-how and have the best prospects for the future.  IMPORTANT FOR US * Professional experience in sea freight; Educational qualification an advantage * Good written and spoken English knowledge * Customer and service orientation * Reliability and friendliness * Responsibility and resilience * Confident use of MS Office programs  IMPORTANT FOR HER * Permanent employment * Interesting projects and a strong team * Varied field of activity * Very good working atmosphere * Punctual and performance-related payment * Training opportunities DENKINGER is a Swabian, family-run logistics company with around 250 employees. With passion, innovation and know-how we create competitive advantages for our business partners. We move goods of all kinds. And when it comes to IT, we create communication structures and platforms that we use to develop individually tailored solutions for each customer. Our goals are sustainable growth and long-term success. That spurs us and our employees on. With their commitment and their ideas, they contribute to our mutual success.  INTERESTED? THEN WE SHOULD GET TO KNOW EACH OTHER ASAP! You can apply by e-mail to bewerbung@denkinger-logistik.de or send you

important * professional experience sea freight ; educational qualification advantage * good write speak english knowledge * customer service orientation * reliability friendliness * responsibility resilience * confident use ms office program important * permanent employment * interesting project strong team * varied field activity * good work atmosphere * punctual performance - relate payment * training opportunity denkinger swabian , family - run logistic company 250 employee .
job description : hire strengthen team specialist ( m / f / d ) global sea freight transport specialist ( m / f / d ) global sea freight transport , networked available advise support customer - ehingen bremerhaven , hybrid remote .
negotiate shipowner , prepare offer , organize freight space connect transport .

Job Description: We are one of the leading medium-sized waste disposal and recycling companies in Baden-Württemberg with currently 6 locations. As a family-run company in Albstadt, we operate a state-of-the-art waste sorting and recycling plant and process alternative fuels. In this way, we actively contribute to environmental protection and significantly to the reduction of greenhouse gases.  Our containers shape the region, our employees the dynamics of our company. Become a part of us at one of our locations in Albstadt, Gammertingen or Riederich  Weighing supervisor / employee scales (m/f/d)

family - run company albstadt , operate state - - - art waste sort recycling plant process alternative fuel .
job description : lead medium - sized waste disposal recycling company baden - württemberg currently 6 location .
location albstadt , gammertingen riederich weighing supervisor / employee scale ( m / f / d )

Job Description: MÜNZING CHEMIE GmbH has been a successful family business since 1830. Today we are represented as a hidden champion on four continents. More than 350 employees in Germany are responsible for the production of high-quality chemical additives. With our additives, we create added value for our wide range of customers from the coatings and paints industry, paper manufacturers and manufacturers of construction chemical products. To strengthen our team we are looking for you  Employee Product Safety Chemical Additives (m/f/x) at our Abstatt location.  The chemistry is right - in our international technology and administration center in Abstatt, you will work on product safety and regulatory issues across all locations.  your area of ​​responsibility * Creation and maintenance of safety data sheets and labels according to CLP/GHS * Maintenance of safety-relevant data of substances, raw materials and products in the existing IT landscape * Determination of the classification of our products and determination of the necessary labeling according to the current national and international chemical legislation * Comparison of the ingredients of our products with national registers of substances * Handling customer inquiries on chemical product safety * Communication with suppliers, customers and consultants  your profile * Successfully completed vocational training as a chemical-technical assistant, chemical laboratory assistant, chemical technician (f/m/d) or comparable qualification * First professional experience in the field of regulatory affairs * Strong analytical skills, quick comprehension and very careful way of working * Ability to work in a team, flexibility, initiative and good organizational skills * Safe handling of MS Office is assumed * Good knowledge of spoken and written German and English what we offer you * Industry standard pay and 30 days vacation * Long-term account * Flexitime model for the right balance between family and work * Fruit basket and free drinks, JobRad, charging stations for your electric car, financial and personal support for (part-time) further training and other benefits * Varied (project) tasks offer interesting development opportunities * Intensive, personal training by a mentor (m/f/d) * Working together on challenging projects with lively and open exchange in the team * Pleasant working atmosphere * Convenient motorway connection  We look forward to receiving your application!  Please send your comprehensive application, including information on your availability and your salary expectations, by email to bewerbung@munzing.com (max. 10 MB, permitted file formats .pdf, .docx, .jpg). Any questions?  Our personnel officer Andrea Wolpert will be happy to answer them on 07131 987-270. MÜNZING CHEMIE GmbH Münzingstrasse 2 74232 Abstatt Detailed information at www.munzing.com

Job Description: Cooperation Officer (m/f/d)  * Rostock * Presence / Mobile * Full time    The UKA Group has around 880 employees and is active in Europe, North and South America. As a full developer, UKA covers the entire value chain and also operates wind and solar parks itself. The company, founded in 1999, is one of the leading German project developers and currently has an onshore wind project pipeline of around 1.8 gigawatts in the approval process in Germany. UKA has also grown internationally in recent years. The current project pipeline of the UKA Group for wind and solar projects now includes more than 14 gigawatts. Your tasks  * Support for project development (wind, PV and grid) on cooperation topics * Coordination and organization of ongoing collaborations * Interdisciplinary coordination in the company * Networking and maintaining contact with external partners * Participation in the initiation, development and consolidation of business relationships * Coordination of project reviews and evaluations * Development of new strategic approaches * Further development of processes in the area of ​​project acquisition and cooperation  your profile * Completed studies at a university, technical college or vocational academy, e.g. public relations / communication management, environmental law, business administration (business administration) or comparable training * Strong communication and organizational skills * Enjoy interdisciplinary work with the willingness to familiarize yourself with new areas of responsibility * Quick comprehension, overarching thinking and a keen eye for the essentials * an independent way of working * Good to very good knowledge of MS Office applications * Basic knowledge of contract law is desirable, but not a requirement We offer you * a multifaceted area of ​​responsibility * A performance-related salary and 30 days vacation * Subject-specific further training opportunities tailored to your needs * Voluntary social benefits (company pension scheme, job ticket, company bicycle) * Opportunities for home office * modern office equipment, free drinks * regular team events * Very good connection to public transport Prior knowledge and professional experience in the field of developing projects for the use of renewable energies, especially wind energy, are desirable but not essential. A company is only as good as its employees. That's why we don't care about gender, skin color, religion or origin. In order to be able to help shape the future of renewable energies in the long term, what counts for us are commitment and competence. Let's work together to successfully implement the energy transition!  Apply now quickly and easily with just a few clicks.  * Hagen Bierstedt * CRE * +49 3521 72806-623 UKA Environmentally Friendly Kraftanlagen GmbH & Co. Job Description: With an annual program of around 5,000 events, the adult education center in Stuttgart is the largest in Baden-Württemberg and one of the largest adult education centers in Germany. As a public further education institution funded by the state capital of Stuttgart, it provides a wide range of educational opportunities related to the city and the educational needs of the citizens with close links to culture and social affairs. The courses, seminars, courses, individual events and series of events in the program areas of general and political education, cultural education, health education, languages ​​(especially German as a foreign language/integration), professional training and further education as well as basic education and school degrees are attended by more than 200,000 people every year . The participants can choose between face-to-face and online courses as well as hybrid formats. On behalf of the state capital Stuttgart, the vhs coordinates the cultural program in its central event building TREFFPUNKT Rotebühlplatz in the center of Stuttgart. In addition, the Volkshochschule stuttgart supports the largest night school in Baden-Württemberg with around 400 students per year. The offers of the children's meeting point and the vhs Ökostation as well as the large inclusive offer round off the spectrum.  For the subject of event coordination at TREFFPUNKT Rotebühlplatz we are looking for a person as soon as possible  Event Technology Team Leader (m/f/d)

course , seminar , course , individual event series event program area general political education , cultural education , health education , language ​​(especially german foreign language / integration ) , professional training education basic education school degree attend 200,000 people year .
