Job Description: Hire to make town. The Kiel Human Resources and Organization Office is looking for support  Hire as HR developer (remunerated according to EG 12 TVöD / A 12 SHBesG)  and become part of the Kiel city administration for an unlimited period of time full/part-time. The state capital Kiel is one of the largest employers and training companies in Schleswig-Holstein and currently employs more than 5,000 people in 27 offices, departments and companies. A family-friendly human resources policy in the form of part-time opportunities and mobile work, as well as a variety of jobs, an extensive training program and an additional pension scheme at the VBL are just a few of the advantages that the Kiel city administration offers. Kiel is a dynamic, cosmopolitan and rapidly growing city with more than 248,000 inhabitants and a high quality of life thanks to its unique location on the fjord.  What we offer - your advantages  • a diverse field of work that requires and desires active participation • a dynamic administration that trusts itself and its employees to change • the opportunity to combine family, free time and everyday work into a meaningful whole • varied sport and fitness offers • Flexible working hours in the context of changing processes and areas of responsibility • tailor-made commuter support - via job ticket or support for private bicycle procurement (including e-bikes) What to do - your new task • You are responsible for the conception and implementation as well as evaluation and, if necessary, adjustment of organizational and personnel development measures. • You advise employees and managers. • You introduce personnel development tools (e.g. knowledge management, e-learning, new work and advancement models) with the involvement of other offices and the responsible bodies. • You supervise and evaluate established programs of personnel development and develop them further. • You develop suitable information and communication concepts, coordinate them and implement them. • You select and commission external consultants, coaches and/or experts.  What you bring with you - your qualifications
Your contact for technical questions about the position is: Dr. Timo Rosenberg, Tel. 0431 901 1001.  Julia Holborn, Tel. 0431 901 5294, is responsible for the recruitment team.
Requirements for Applicant: 
Basic knowledge: Office communication MS Office
Advanced knowledge: personnel development

offer - advantage • diverse field work require desire active participation • dynamic administration trust employee change • opportunity combine family , free time everyday work meaningful • varied sport fitness offer • flexible work hour context change process area responsibility •
tailor - commuter support - job ticket support private bicycle procurement ( include e - bike ) - new task • responsible conception implementation evaluation , necessary , adjustment organizational personnel development measure .
family - friendly human resource policy form - time opportunity mobile work , variety job , extensive training program additional pension scheme vbl advantage kiel city administration offer .

Job Description: We are looking for operations managers for our glamping locations, ideally with previous experience in the hotel or catering industry, but career changers are very welcome.
The company for premium camping currently operates two campsites, the out on the lake: spaden near Bremerhaven, and the out and well: casel in Brandenburg.  Do you have experience in project management, maybe you have led a team before and are you not easily ruffled anyway? Do you like to take on responsibility, like a bit of adventure and like a breath of fresh air? Then we have the right job for you.  In our camps you are responsible for the smooth running of guest care and lead a small team of employees. Accommodation and food will be provided by us. Your location is the location, ideally in 2 or 3 week shifts.
Requirements for Applicant: 
Advanced knowledge: Project management

job description : look operation manager glamping location , ideally previous experience hotel catering industry , career changer welcome .
company premium camping currently operate campsite , lake : spaden near bremerhaven , : casel brandenburg .

Job Description: You are a trained electronics technician, electrician, electrical system fitter, electrical installer, system electronics technician or have another electrical profession. Are you looking for or are you interested in a varied job without shift and weekend work with an employer who values ​​your work? enerix is ​​the leading specialist company for photovoltaic systems in the northern Upper Palatinate. enerix has been installing photovoltaic systems on the roofs of its customers for 15 years, helping them to obtain clean and cost-effective electricity. We are a team in which you can rely on one another and in which everyone meets at eye level.  As an electronics technician, you expand your skills and learn how to install photovoltaic systems and electricity storage. You will work with our experienced colleagues and qualify for the safe and promising solar industry. From electronics engineer to expert for photovoltaic systems  As an electronics technician for building technology, you are a professional for electrical systems in buildings. At enerix you use and expand your knowledge and are responsible for the electrical connection of photovoltaic systems, battery storage and charging stations in our customers' houses.  If glitches occur, you dig into the system and find the cause. Equipped with branded tools, a high-quality service vehicle and modern work clothes, you will work independently in a team.
Requirements for Applicant: 
Basic knowledge: electrical installation

job description : train electronic technician , electrician , electrical system fitter , electrical installer , system electronic technician electrical profession .
electronics engineer expert photovoltaic system electronics technician build technology , professional electrical system building .
enerix use expand knowledge responsible electrical connection photovoltaic system , battery storage charge station customer ' house .

Apply to us You will receive a call from us promptly.  Your tasks - Production and assembly of metal and plastic parts according to specifications - Processing of light metals and steel according to technical drawings - Servicing, care and maintenance of the production facilities - Scribing, cutting and shaping metal parts - Implementation of quality controls and, if necessary, error corrections Our requirements  - Successfully completed training as a metal worker (m/f/d) or a comparable qualification - Ideally, practical experience in an equivalent position - Ability to work in a team and work independently - Accurate and thorough way of working  We look forward to you!
Requirements for Applicant: 
Basic knowledge: maintenance, repair, maintenance, metal construction

task - production assembly metal plastic part accord specification - processing light metal steel accord technical drawing - servicing , care maintenance production facility - scribing , cut shape metal part - implementation quality control , necessary , error correction requirement - successfully complete training metal worker ( m / f / d ) comparable qualification - ideally , practical experience equivalent position - ability work team work independently - accurate thorough way work look forward !

Job Description: Health is our greatest asset We – for life  BERLIN-CHEMIE AG belongs to the Italian Menarini Group and researches, produces and sells pharmaceutical products in more than 30 countries. Our commitment to health is what unites the many different employees in our company. With our responsible work, we ensure that patients can rely on us. Because we stand for life. USE YOUR POTENTIAL AS A Medical Assistant International (m/f/d) location Berlin subject area International career level young professionals time of entry from now on contract type temporary working hours full time home office Home office possible time of entry from now on contract type temporary working hours full time home office Home office possible  Your tasks You will support our medical team and the Drug Safety Coordinating Unit with daily tasks and general office organization. Due to your organizational talent, you ensure the timely processing of invoice management and the legalization of documents and take over the organization of business trips and appointments.  Another focus of your work is on conducting literature research and systematically archiving and distributing the resulting results. You support the provision of medical and scientific information materials and coordinate the updating and maintenance of documents for drug approval. In this context, you coordinate the translation of scientific documentation and support the creation of training materials and presentations. You bring your very good knowledge of English to bear in your day-to-day work and in communicating with our foreign organizations as needed.  You are interested in a job in which you have insights into and points of contact with international medical and scientific topics and combine them with varied office work. You see yourself as a reliable and flexible contact person who is happy to provide advice and assistance.  The advertised position is limited as part of a parental leave replacement until January 31, 2025. your profile  * Completed commercial vocational training * First professional experience in team assistance * Knowledge of the pharmaceutical market or initial experience in the pharmaceutical industry * Excellent communication and teamwork skills * structured way of working * Very good knowledge of spoken and written English * Knowledge of Russian is an advantage * Very good knowledge of MS Office    What you benefit from * to make a contribution to improving the quality of life of many people with their own work in a future-oriented industry * professional Welcome Days for an optimal start and a structured familiarization with your tasks * Transnational cooperation with family togetherness & freedom to help shape your own work * Targeted further training, cross-departmental insights and opportunities for networking within the company * Regulated & flexible handling of working hours, 30 days vacation, very good collectively agreed remuneration and other benefits such as holiday and Christmas bonuses * Company restaurant with a variety of healthy dishes and fresh barista coffee for in between meals Our offer convinces you? Then become part of us. We look forward to your informative online application.  Application tips How to reach your goal Extensive and well supported Benefits  With us, not only an attractive and collectively agreed remuneration awaits you. We offer a comprehensive package of employer benefits from A for old-age provision to Z for allowances. CONTACT Juliane Soika HR Expert 030 6707-3151 Berlin-Chemie AG  Glienicker Weg 125 12489 Berlin Telephone 030 6707-3600   career.berlin-chemistry.de

knowledge pharmaceutical market initial experience pharmaceutical industry * excellent communication teamwork skill * structured way work * good knowledge spoken write english * knowledge russian advantage * good knowledge ms office benefit * contribution improve quality life people work future - orient industry

Job Description: The REGIOMED Medical Care Centers (MVZ) ensure that the people in our region receive outpatient medical care close to where they live, under municipal sponsorship. At a total of 15 locations in southern Thuringia and Upper Franconia, we treat our patients in various family and specialist disciplines. We see ourselves as a cooperation partner for resident doctors, outpatient aid and health services, and the clinics that provide further treatment. Our responsibility focuses on high-quality patient care and reliability as an employer for our employees. Job Description: 
The tasks include answering the incoming calls at the head office and various central administrative services, e.g. e.g.: • the opening and distribution of the daily incoming mail • the processing of daily outgoing mail • checking tank receipts and entering them into an Excel file • Preparatory work for other departments • Monitoring of tenders • Keeping attendance lists • the forwarding of e-mails • the reception of visitors • stock control of office supplies • Applying for and managing certificates ... and other tasks that arise.  It is important to us that you appear friendly and courteous, both on the phone and when dealing with colleagues and customers. Good communication skills in German, both written and spoken, as well as confident handling of the common MS Office programs are prerequisites. Team spirit and flexibility complete the profile.
Requirements for Applicant: 
Basic knowledge: telephone service
Advanced knowledge: Mail processing, office and administrative work, scheduling and monitoring

job description : task include answer incoming call head office central administrative service , e.g. e.g. : • opening distribution daily incoming mail • processing daily outgoing mail • checking tank receipt enter excel file • preparatory work department • monitoring tender • keep attendance list • forwarding e - mail • reception visitor • stock control office supply • apply manage certificate ...
requirement applicant : basic knowledge : telephone service advanced knowledge : mail processing , office administrative work , scheduling monitoring
good communication skill german , write speak , confident handling common ms office program prerequisite .

Job Description: Are you a goal-oriented team player? Do you not only master your field of work, but also want to act independently?  Our claim and goal is to solve problems for our clients and to find the most economically sensible solution. The trust of our clients forms the decisive basis for a successful cooperation. We, a medium-sized auditing and tax consulting company with four locations, specialize in restructuring and crisis consulting as well as advising insolvency administrators; who we support with tax issues in insolvency, the preparation and audit of annual financial statements, with going concern and restructuring.  To strengthen our team in Dresden, we are now looking for someone Assistant to the tax consultant (f/m/d) Gladly with professional experience in full or part time.  Your tasks  Preparation of annual financial statements, income surplus calculations and company tax returns  Support for professionals with tax advice, legal remedies and tax audits, etc.  your qualification  Successfully completed training as a tax clerk, tax specialist, accountant, Bachelor of Arts (WiWi), MBA or comparable  Application-ready knowledge in the areas of accounting and taxes  Service orientation and pleasure in client contact  Commitment and independent working methods  IT skills, especially DATEV and MS Excel Do you feel addressed?  Then become part of our team. In addition to a challenging, demanding and interesting job as well as individual training opportunities, you can expect flexible working hours, performance-related remuneration, social benefits and other company advantages, such as very good transport connections, free parking spaces and drinks.
Requirements for Applicant: 
Basic knowledge: business administration
Advanced knowledge: spreadsheet Excel (MS Office), annual financial statements, bookkeeping, bookkeeping, Datev program merchandise management, tax law

addition challenging , demanding interesting job individual training opportunity , expect flexible working hour , performance - relate remuneration , social benefit company advantage , good transport connection , free parking space drink .

Your tasks at a glance...  - Maintenance and repair work is carried out professionally by you - You assemble and disassemble components and assemblies - Tests and corresponding documentation are also part of your area of ​​activity - You work to work order. Job Description: We are looking for... ...for a well-known chemical company, a global manufacturer of color pigments for the construction industry, based in Krefeld-Chempark, production assistant with forklift license (m/f/d). The position is to be filled as part of temporary employment and full-time.  Your tasks... - Bigpacks have to be filled - You transport different containers, big packs on pallets using forklifts and store them - The production colleagues will be supported by you - Any clearing and cleaning work will be carried out by you - They take samples and carry out checks. Your profile...  - You have already gained experience in the field of production - Experience in the field of chemistry is desirable - You have a forklift license - Shift work is not a problem for you, it is not absolutely necessary - You are characterized by a reliable and team-oriented way of working We are committed to employing people with severe disabilities. For this reason, severely disabled and equivalent applicants with the same qualifications are given preferential consideration. We offer...  - An attractive starting wage of 17 EUR/h increasing up to 22.30 EUR/h plus surcharges for alternating/conti shifts - Additional holiday and Christmas bonuses - A job with a well-known chemical company as a stepping stone to a permanent position - Your Piing Team Krefeld will provide you with comprehensive support on all work-related topics - We take care of your necessary G-examinations as well as work clothes. 2022 awarded with the Great Place to Work® We look forward to receiving your complete application, including your CV and the earliest possible starting date.
Requirements for Applicant: 
Basic knowledge: distilling (chemistry), extracting, extracting, refining
Advanced knowledge: warehouse work, forklifts (diesel, petrol, electrical, gas), chemical process engineering

Our almost 200 full-time and 130 volunteer employees do great things every day. We are strong as a partner of people on their way to a successful life - with commitment, competence and passion. We stand for equal opportunities, self-determination and participation. Would you like to be part of the whole and get involved professionally? Then you are exactly right with us. For the holiday camp of our educational centers from 23.07.2023 to 06.08.2023 in Prerow we are looking for: Holiday camp supervisor (m/f/d). Your tasks are: The loving, warm and humorous accompaniment and care of our children aged 6 to 12 years in the above mentioned. Period Leisure and holiday activities by the sea in coordination with the male colleague, offering games and activities depending on the weather conditions Help for the younger children with everyday activities Educational training / educational studies or a youth leader card Reliability and joie de vivre Calmness and resilience A driver's license Class B A current first aid certificate Then we look forward to working with you! An unforgettable holiday by the sea Compensation based on a trainer flat rate Board and lodging on site, travel included

Job Description: Would you like more time to care for your clients, more relaxed work, personal and professional development or a job where you can say "That's why I became a nurse"?  —  ✔ That's what we offer you
• Sufficient time for the outpatient care of your client and for yourself through the model of 1: 1 care  • Stay technically fit. We offer a wide range of courses and further training opportunities, e.g. B. the non-clinical basic course • Ambulatory and home work environments where you can provide the help that is needed locally  •    As a nursing service that operates throughout Germany, you can be sure of your job with us even in times of crisis  • Permanent employment contract so that you can plan your life in the long term • Our heroes in care achieve a lot. When it comes to salary, you won't miss out with us  • With your Sunday and public holiday bonuses, an appropriate balance is ensured • Look forward to more money at the end of the month due to the night shift surcharge  • A better work-life balance is ensured with regulated duty times and uncomplicated co-creation of your duty rosters  • As a bipG nurse, you benefit from numerous discounts when shopping online via our employee portal, e.g. B. at CEWE PHOTOBOOK or Jochen Schweizer ✔ Your tasks  • Enable your client to lead an individual and self-determined life. You carry out basic, treatment and activation care independently and document care data ✔ Your profile  • You are a registered nurse, nurse, nurse (m/f/d) or geriatric nurse —
Become part of our bipG team as a part-time or full-time nurse for outpatient intensive care and 1: 1 care in Dorsten. Day shifts and night shifts are possible in 12-hour shifts. How do you apply? Quickly and easily by...  ✔ Email >> bewerbung(a)bipg.de ✔ Call >> 0511 12331410 ✔www.bipg.de/online-werbung/ Do you have any questions about us or the position? We are happy to answer your questions over the phone.  Your contact Aleksandr Cabanov  —
Requirements for Applicant: 
Basic knowledge: basic care, treatment care, care documentation
Advanced knowledge: patient care

carry basic , treatment activation care independently document care datum ✔ profile • register nurse , nurse , nurse ( m / f / d ) geriatric nurse — bipg team - time - time nurse outpatient intensive care 1 : 1 care dorsten .
offer wide range course training opportunity , e.g. b. non - clinical basic course • ambulatory home work environment provide help need locally • nursing service operate germany , sure job time crisis • permanent employment contract plan life long term • hero care achieve lot .
well work - life balance ensure regulate duty time uncomplicated co - creation duty roster • bipg nurse , benefit numerous discount shop online employee portal , e.g. b. cewe photobook jochen schweizer ✔ task • enable client lead individual self - determine life .

Job Description: We are currently looking for CNC specialists for our business partners in the Limburg region. Your tasks  - Machining of workpieces - Carrying out measurements and tests - Programming, operation and monitoring of computer-controlled lathes - Execution of test runs - Maintenance and care of the machines  Our requirements - Completed training as a CNC specialist (m/f/d) or a comparable qualification - Work experience in a comparable position- Ideally knowledge of reading drawings - Manual dexterity desirable - Independent and careful way of working We look forward to receiving your application!
Requirements for Applicant: 
Advanced knowledge: CNC knowledge, CNC programming

task - machining workpiece - carry measurement test - programming , operation monitoring computer - control lathe - execution test run - maintenance care machine requirement - complete training cnc specialist ( m / f / d ) comparable qualification - work experience comparable position- ideally knowledge read drawing - manual dexterity desirable - independent careful way work look forward receive application !
requirement applicant : advanced knowledge : cnc knowledge , cnc programming
job description : currently look cnc specialist business partner limburg region .

Job Description: 
Company The BBHT consulting company is a management consultancy that supports customers from strategic advice to professional, technical implementation. Our focus is on the implementation of IT projects. We specialize in the banking and insurance, telecommunications and healthcare sectors. BBHT consultants are experienced business analysts and project managers who are technically and professionally highly qualified, socially competent and good at communicating. We are looking for you as a management consultant (m/f/d) in Münster, Frankfurt or remote Münster Full-time tasks Independent advice, management and implementation of our customers' banking and insurance projects Recording, analysis and conception of requirements, coordination with the project team and Stakeholders Active support in the implementation of legal & regulatory requirements Cooperation in partnership & open communication with our customers Requirements In-depth & several years of experience in the banking or insurance industry Extensive methodical & conceptual experience & skills in project management or in business analysis Independent & communicative personality with IT affinity and willingness to travel We offer a good work-life balance through flexible working hours, paid overtime & 30 days of holiday office days, home office, MacBook, iPhone, company car or bicycle, 1st class rail card if required, free snacks & drinks in the office Qualified regular further training, participation in IT conferences & company events A permanent position in a highly motivated team Independent work, challenging & innovative projects with well-known customers Have we aroused your interest? We offer you a unique opportunity to get involved in an innovative environment and to develop yourself further. Our team looks forward to getting to know you and benefiting from your know-how and enthusiasm. We are looking forward to your application! APPLY HERE Contact person: Enrico Funnekötter BBHTberatungsgesellschaft mbH & Co. KG Am Mittelhafen 14 • 48155 Münster

Job Description: The DRK child, youth and family services in OWL gGmbH are responsible for 5 open all-day schools in the city of Bielefeld. For the facilities in BI-Sennestadt we are now looking for a Everyday helper (f/m/d).  The position is limited until July 31, 2023.  It awaits you • A part-time position of up to 30 hours • Annual special payments • Supplementary pension fund • A varied workplace in friendly teams
Requirements for Applicant: 
Basic knowledge: cleaning, everyday support, leisure activities

await • - time position 30 hour • annual special payment • supplementary pension fund • varied workplace friendly team requirement applicant : basic knowledge : cleaning , everyday support , leisure activity
job description : drk child , youth family service owl ggmbh responsible 5 open - day school city bielefeld .
facility bi - sennestadt look everyday helper ( f / m / d ) .

Job Description: We at Coronia are not just looking for employees - we are looking for YOU!  For a well-known company in the Biberach area, we are looking for industrial painters (f/m/d) who are true Picassos with the airless gun. People who WHAT DO WE OFFER - A permanent position until you are taken over by the partner company. - A good job in a down-to-earth, future-oriented company. - Fair payment based on the "performance is worth it" principle. - Annual increases in social benefits such as Christmas and holiday bonuses. - A day shift workplace accessible by public transport.  THOSE ARE YOUR TASKS - Mixtures of paints - Priming and painting in the airless process - Quality control of the painted parts  YOUR SKILLS - You have successfully completed an apprenticeship as an industrial painter (f/m/d) or have a comparable qualification. - You have a good feel for cup guns. - You are motivated and reliable. - You are very handy with your hands. - A good team is the be-all and end-all for you. Take your chance and apply to us today! You can either send us an email (werbung@coronia.de), call us (0731/715 75 0) or use the apply button. All applicants are equally welcome.
Requirements for Applicant: 
Basic knowledge: machine management, system management and operation, spray painting, varnishing, corrosion protection

tasks - mixtures paint - priming painting airless process - quality control paint part skills - successfully complete apprenticeship industrial painter ( f / m / d ) comparable qualification .
job description : coronia look employee - look ! - know company biberach area , look industrial painter ( f / m / d ) true picassos airless gun .
- good job - - earth , future - orient company .

Job Description: Join our team in university communications as soon as possible Digital Student Recruitment Specialist (m/f/d)  Salary group E11 TV-L | Part-time (50%) | initially limited to 2 years with the option of an extension  THE TEAM The university communications team currently consists of four people. We have an open, appreciative culture of communication and work in close cooperation in a team or with the other areas of the university in a solution-oriented manner. We meet our daily challenge of successfully designing and further developing the processes of internal and external communication and the central event management at the university with commitment and customer orientation.  YOUR TASKS • You independently carry out market analyzes for the courses offered by the university. • You will implement digital marketing strategies and measures for all strategically relevant communication channels in accordance with the HWG LU's holistic marketing concept, based on the latest, target group-oriented digital trends. • You plan and implement paid online marketing campaigns (especially SEA and paid social media) • You create, among other things in direct exchange with students, target group-specific content, especially for campaigns in social networks. • You control and optimize digital marketing activities in a performance-oriented manner based on tracking data and KPIs. • You will provide conceptual, organizational and content support for the relaunch of the central university website planned for 2023/2024, particularly with the coordination and implementation of internal and external coordination processes. • You coordinate the marketing activities closely with the university communications team and the university management and integrate them into the university processes.  YOUR PROFILE Necessary degree • You have a bachelor's or master's degree in economics with a strong focus on marketing. Experience • You have initial professional experience in online marketing with knowledge of the current tools and methods. • Ideally, you have experience in marketing for typical university target groups and experience in the field of communication. expertise • You have in-depth knowledge of the methods used to develop marketing strategies and how to implement them. • You have in-depth knowledge of the performance-oriented development, implementation and optimization of online marketing campaigns in relevant online media channels. • You have in-depth knowledge of creating online marketing content and using it. • Experience in Typo 3 or another CMS is an advantage. • You have very good knowledge of English.  personal • You are strong in communication, presentation and negotiation, confident in your appearance and like to approach people. • You are enthusiastic about creative, target group-specific content and like to continuously develop new ideas. • You enjoy implementing new concepts. • You are actively involved in the team. • You are an organizational talent, resilient and can deal well with occasional time pressure. OUR RANGE  An interesting area of ​​responsibility in a motivated team and a family atmosphere An attractive working environment with flexible working time and place of work, modern equipment and numerous offers in health management The promotion of your professional and personal development through extensive personnel development measures An attractive university location with good transport links, free parking and a daycare center The remuneration is based on salary group 11 TV-L, provided that the professional and personal requirements are met. You will receive a collective annual special payment and an additional pension. The annual salary depends on your professional experience and is (part-time with classification in E 11) at least €43,830 gross. (€46,780 in year 2)  In addition, the general requirements for employment in the public sector apply. The Ludwigshafen University of Economics and Society is certified as a family-friendly university. Qualified female applicants are expressly encouraged to apply. Applicants with severe disabilities will be given preference if they are equally qualified. YOUR APPLICATION  Are you addressing these prospects? Then we look forward to receiving your online application with a letter of motivation, curriculum vitae, certificates and indication of the earliest possible starting date by March 6th, 2023 via our application portal. The interviews are scheduled for the end of March 2023.
Requirements for Applicant: 
Advanced knowledge: Marketing, search engine optimization (SEO), search engine advertising (SEA), online marketing

• plan implement pay online marketing campaign ( especially sea pay social medium ) • create , thing direct exchange student , target group - specific content , especially campaign social network .
range interesting area ​​responsibility motivated team family atmosphere attractive working environment flexible working time place work , modern equipment numerous offer health management promotion professional personal development extensive personnel development measure attractive university location good transport link , free parking daycare center remuneration base salary group 11 tv - l , provide professional personal requirement meet .

Job Description: View job here Software Tester (m/f/d) * Full time * Rosenstrasse 5-9, 65189 Wiesbaden, Germany * With professional experience * 02/17/23 For our quality management department, we are looking for a software tester (m/f/d) in Wiesbaden as soon as possible. Your tasks  * Participation in setting up a quality management system with a special focus on IT systems and workflows * Carrying out technical reviews as well as system, integration and acceptance tests for new acquisitions or modifications of IT systems * Creation and execution of test concepts, test cases, test specifications and test scenarios as well as selection of suitable test methods and test procedures * Involvement in projects, independent implementation of sub-projects * Participation in the system supervision service  your profile * Successfully completed studies in (business) computer science * Very good knowledge of methods and the implementation of software testing * Very good analytical and conceptual skills * Independent and result-oriented work * Good English knowledge what we offer you * Autonomous work in a performance-oriented, dynamic and team-oriented work environment * Attractive remuneration and good social benefits (e.g. company pension scheme, childcare allowance) * Flexible working hours * Flat hierarchies and an open, cooperative atmosphere

task * participation set quality management system special focus system workflow * carry technical review system , integration acceptance test new acquisition modification system * creation execution test concept , test case , test specification test scenario selection suitable test method test procedure * involvement project , independent implementation sub - project * participation system supervision service profile * successfully complete study ( business ) computer science * good knowledge method implementation software testing * good analytical conceptual skill * independent result - orient work * good english knowledge offer * autonomous work performance - orient , dynamic team - orient work environment * attractive remuneration good social benefit ( e.g. company pension scheme , childcare allowance )

Job Description: You make the difference. The automated judicial dunning procedure (AGM) is a modern and citizen-friendly service of the judiciary. With our transnational e-government application, we have been offering the citizens and businesses of the Federal Republic of Germany the opportunity for 40 years to have outstanding monetary claims determined by the court in a title suitable for enforcement (§§ 688 ff. ZPO) . We at the ICT specialist center for justice have set ourselves the goal of creating and developing a sustainable IT infrastructure for the Baden-Württemberg judiciary and thus establishing the key technologies of the 21st century in the judiciary.
Requirements for Applicant: 
Basic knowledge: Security systems (IT), data security, customer advice and support
Advanced knowledge: Agile project management, system software (development, programming, analysis), database development, programming, quality management, information technology, computer technology, user advice, user support (IT), software testing, computer science

requirement applicant : basic knowledge : security system ( ) , data security , customer advice support advanced knowledge : agile project management , system software ( development , programming , analysis ) , database development , programming , quality management , information technology , computer technology , user advice , user support ( ) , software testing , computer science
transnational e - government application , offer citizen business federal republic germany opportunity 40 year outstanding monetary claim determine court title suitable enforcement ( § § 688 ff .
ict specialist center justice set goal create develop sustainable infrastructure baden - württemberg judiciary establish key technology 21st century judiciary .

Job Description: About Buemann Personal Service We, the company Buemann Personal Service GmbH, have been active in the Upper Swabia and Allgäu region since 2007 in the field of personnel recruitment and hiring. Since then we have grown steadily. We are proud to count numerous, well-known companies from the region among our customer base. Fair, appreciative and successful cooperation - that's what we stand for. Our approximately 250 satisfied employees as well as the numerous takeovers in a permanent position speak for us.  Benefit from our know-how  Production assistant m/f/d

Regardless of whether you are a skilled worker, an assistant, a young professional or a returnee, we will find the right job for you. We have been matching the right candidates with the right jobs for over 25 years. From the very beginning, employee satisfaction has been the top priority. With us, you are not just one of many personnel numbers – you are part of the family! You will not only benefit from our constantly growing network of companies and interesting job offers, but you will also receive detailed and continuous advice from our experts about your development and further training opportunities. Your application is the first step in a long-term and successful cooperation.  Have we piqued your interest? Then get in touch with us today and arrange your personal consultation (in person, by telephone or via video conference). You can reach us free of charge at 0800-STUBNER (0800-7882637) or jobs(a)stubner-personalservice.deYour team at STUBNERpersonalservice GmbH looks forward to seeing you!

Job Description: Josef Rädlinger Bauunternehmen GmbH belongs to the financially strong and powerful Josef Rädlinger group of companies with around 2,000 employees at 8 locations. Our range of services includes traffic routes, asphalt and civil engineering, planning, building construction, network and pipeline construction as well as horizontal drilling technology. We also offer raw and auxiliary materials.
Requirements for Applicant: 
Advanced knowledge: construction equipment management, construction machine management, excavators, suction excavators

range service include traffic route , asphalt civil engineering , planning , build construction , network pipeline construction horizontal drilling technology .
requirement applicant : advanced knowledge : construction equipment management , construction machine management , excavator , suction excavator

Job Description: AROUND TOWN COMMERCIAL PROPERTIES (ATCP)  ATCP is a company of the Aroundtown Group. The commercial real estate division brings together experts from all areas of real estate management. The teams put together in a targeted manner develop the best strategy for each property and implement it in full. The in-house range of services includes letting, asset, property and construction management, development as well as rent accounting, controlling and utility bills. Our specialized teams also advise companies of all sizes in the search for suitable space and the flexible design and implementation of space concepts. Teamlead Project Management Construction (m/f/d)

- house range service include let , asset , property construction management , development rent accounting , controlling utility bill .

Job Description: Are you a production mechanic looking for a new professional challenge in Limburg? Then you are exactly right with us. Apply to us You will receive a call from us promptly.  Your tasks  - Manufacture of molds and components in the field of sintered metal - Setup, programming and operation of the CNC machines - Maintenance and care of the production facilities - Reading technical drawings - Implementation of quality controls and, if necessary, error corrections Our requirements  - Successfully completed training as an industrial mechanic, cutting machine operator or a comparable qualification - ideally practical experience in an equivalent job - Willingness to work in shifts - Ability to work in a team and work independently - Accurate and thorough way of working  We look forward to you!
Requirements for Applicant: 
Advanced knowledge: maintenance, repair, servicing

Job Description: True, working with dynamic people is not child's play. If creativity is your superpower and you're used to staying calm even in the midst of a mess, then you could be a good fit for us. We are looking for open-minded people with imagination and understanding who would like to develop further - personally and professionally. To do this, we form strong teams in which it is noticeable that everyone is pulling in the same direction.
We are a large aid organization headquartered in Berlin. Our tasks include Rescue and first aid service, care offers, civil protection, social services and work with children and young people. Further information on entry opportunities, perspectives and how we work: johanniter.de/karriere

You have come to the right place. Save yourself tedious individual applications and benefit from our knowledge of the market and our passion for advice!  For our customer, a biotechnology company based in Munich, we are looking for a full-time quality manager (m/f/d) to support the team. The search is within the framework of temporary employment.
Requirements for Applicant: 
Advanced knowledge: Scheduling, monitoring, correspondence, creating presentation documents
Expert knowledge: quality management

Job Description: We are looking for reinforcement for our team! We offer permanent part-time employment in an owner-managed and employee-oriented company with flexible working hours (MON - THURS 5 hours each 8 a.m. - 1 p.m., 9 a.m. - 2 p.m. or 10 a.m. - 3 p.m.).  An ideal re-entry into working life for mothers and fathers who have children in KITA, KIGA or school. We also welcome applications from experienced professionals who would like to start again when the children are able to stand on their own two feet. Your tasks will focus on accounting and general office administration; Good to very good knowledge of English is an advantage, as we work in an international environment.  As a certification company, we attach great importance to the high quality of the services we provide to our customers.  We offer you ... ...  very good general conditions (flexible working hours ...  Home office by arrangement, in case a child is ill ... holiday and Christmas bonuses) in a stable company ... Collegial cooperation in our existing team ...  a varied work environment ... short lines of communication and flat hierarchies are a matter of course for us
We are looking forward to your contact. For more information about our company, please visit our website: www.ajaregistrars.de
Requirements for Applicant: 
Basic knowledge: social media communication, administration, payment transactions, human resources
Advanced knowledge: billing, bookkeeping, bookkeeping, mail processing, word processing, reporting, information, office and administrative work, office supplies management, office organization, office management, e-mail communication, correspondence, correspondence, customer advice and support, scheduling and monitoring, secretarial work , assistant

Job Description: Clerks in the Office for General Citizens' Affairs (m/f/d)  Your main tasks Processing of resident registration matters at the counter Processing of registrations, cancellations and change of registrations Handling passport and identity card matters Provision of information from the population register Processing of applications for certificates of good conduct and information from the central business register We offer you Remuneration according to salary group A 7 or salary group 6 of the collective agreement for the public sector (TVöD) with dynamic salary development and individual level assignment according to previous experience, including annual bonus Contribution to supplementary pension 30 vacation days future-proof jobs Flexible working hours (flextime from 6 a.m. to 9 p.m.) taking into account the opening hours of the Citizens’ Affairs department part-time employment mobile working and teleworking Company fitness with Hansefit Workplace Health Promotion Qualify for management positions with our internal training program  your profile Qualification for career group 1, 2nd entry office in the field of general services or successfully completed vocational training as an administrative clerk / administrative clerk or a successfully completed clerk training course I Basic knowledge of registration, passport and identity card law Experiences in dealing with audiences Pronounced IT skills (MS Windows, Word, Excel), which you can prove by means of appropriate training certificates decision-making ability  We stand for
Requirements for Applicant: 
Basic knowledge: Excel spreadsheets (MS Office), word processing Word (MS Office), e-mail program Outlook (MS Office), identification, passport and registration systems, customer advice and support

You have come to the right place. Many years of experience in personnel consulting, the clear focus on the Munich area and our industry-specific specialization with an extensive customer network make us a competent partner when looking for a job. Save yourself tedious individual applications and benefit from our knowledge of the market and our passion for advice!  For our customer, a company in the field of logistics services based in Garching near Munich, we are looking for a full-time project manager (m/f/d) to support the team. The search is within the framework of temporary employment.
Requirements for Applicant: 
Advanced knowledge: project assistance, preparation and organization of meetings, office and administrative work, scheduling and monitoring

Requirements for Applicant: 
Advanced knowledge: Order picking
